<p>The regular dodecahedron is a Platonic solid. Edge length and radius hav=
e the same unit (e.g. meter), the area has this unit squared (e.g. square m=
eter), the volume has this unit to the power of three (e.g. cubic meter). A=
/V has this unit <sup>-1</sup>.</p>
<br><br>
<img src=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/img/net/dodecahedron.png" width=3D"=
300" height=3D"164" alt=3D"Net of a dodecahedron"><br>
Net of a dodecahedron, the three-dimensional body is unfolded in two dimens=
ions.<br><br>
<p>Of the five Platonic solids, the dodecahedron is the one that has the si=
de surfaces with the most corners. This gives it a more spherical appearanc=
e than the other Platonic solids, even compared to the <a href=3D"https://r=
echneronline.de/pi/icosahedron.php">icosahedron</a>, which has more sides a=
nd the same number of edges, but fewer corners.<br>
There are other dodecahedrons with less regularity, including the <a href=
=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/rhombic-dodecahedron.php">rhombic dodecahed=
ron</a> and the <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/snub-disphenoid.php"=
>snub disphenoid</a>. If you extend the edges of the regular dodecahedron u=
ntil they meet, a <a href=3D"https://rechneronline.de/pi/small-stellated-do=
decahedron.php">small stellated dodecahedron</a> is created.<br>
There are dodecahedron-shaped crystals, for example of pyrite and cobaltite=
. The Romans made dodecahedrons of bronze or lead that had <a href=3D"https=
://rechneronline.de/pi/sphere-calculator.php">spheres</a> at their corners =
and were several centimeters in size. Their intended use is still unknown. =
Some dodecahedrons can be found in the architecture and design of indoor an=
d outdoor objects. When assigning the five Platonic solids to the elements =
of ancient Greece, the dodecahedron was associated with the aether, probabl=
y because of its peculiar shape. In addition to the four worldly elements f=
ire, water, earth, air, aether was the quintessence, the fifth element, whi=
ch had no mass and shaped the unchanging cosmic sphere beyond the moon.</p>
